name: proximitybeacon_beacons_diagnostics_list
description: List the diagnostics for a single beacon. You can also list diagnostics for all the beacons owned by your Google Developers Console project by using the beacon name `beacons/-`. Authenticate using an [OAuth access token](https://developers.google.com/identity/protocols/OAuth2) from a signed-in user with **viewer**, **Is owner** or **Can edit** permissions in the Google Developers Console project.

beaconName.description: Beacon that the diagnostics are for.

alertFilter.description: Requests only beacons that have the given alert. For example, to find beacons that have low batteries use `alert_filter=LOW_BATTERY`.

pageSize.description: Specifies the maximum number of results to return. Defaults to 10. Maximum 1000. Optional.

pageToken.description: Requests results that occur after the `page_token`, obtained from the response to a previous request. Optional.

projectId.description: Requests only diagnostic records for the given project id. If not set, then the project making the request will be used for looking up diagnostic records. Optional.

fields.description: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

key.description: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

oauth_token.description: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

prettyPrint.description: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

quotaUser.description: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters.

$block: Response that contains the requested diagnostics.

$ul: **diagnostics**: The diagnostics matching the given request.
**nextPageToken**: Token that can be used for pagination. Returned only if the request matches more beacons than can be returned in this response.
